(Translated by Google) Dear guest, according to the rules of the Ministry of Health of Ukraine, the following criteria apply, according to which you have the right to visit the institution, namely:
1. In the presence of a negative result of testing for COVID-19 by polymerase chain reaction (PCR test) or rapid test for coronavirus antigen SARS-CoV-2, which was conducted no more than 72 hours before visiting the institution;
2. If there is a document confirming receipt of the full course of vaccination, an international, domestic certificate or a foreign certificate confirming vaccination against COVID-19 with one dose of single-dose vaccine or two doses of two-dose vaccine (green certificates) included by the World Health Organization to the list of permitted for use in emergencies;
3. If there is a negative result of testing by polymerase chain reaction or recovery of a person from the disease, the validity of which is confirmed by the Unified State Web Portal of electronic services, in particular using the mobile application of the Portal Action (Action).
And under no circumstances do we have the right to require you to show documents, we only asked and clarified the availability of the above documents. üåªüåºüåª

